The controversy about the best player between Lionel Messi and Cristiano will continue to rage for years after their footballing careers. Argentine superstar, Lionel Messi has been listed as the best player of the 21st Century in a list compiled by Four Four Two magazine. The Paris Saint-Germain (PSG) attacker tops the list ahead of Manchester United’s Cristiano Ronaldo who occupies the second spot. Both Messi and Ronaldo have a total of 12 Ballon d’Or awards between them with the Argentine claiming seven while Ronaldo has five attached to his name. Ronaldo can also boast of winning league titles in three of Europe’s topflight leagues with Manchester United, Real Madrid, and Juventus meanwhile Messi has won with FC Barcelona and most recently with PSG. Meanwhile 2002 World Cup winner, Ronaldinho has been listed as the fifth best player in the 21st Century with the FC Barcelona duo of Iniesta and Xavi ahead of the Brazilian GiveMeSport reports. Zinedine Zidane is listed in the sixth spot while Thierry Henry, Ricardo Kaka, Manuel Neuer, and Luis Suarez occupy the top 10 positions. Bayern Munich’s Robert Lewandowski is 28th, Didier Drogba is in 40th position while Kylian Mbappe is ranked 75th.